reviews.text: 菜单品种不算多，这家特色是炸猪排！

This is a strip down version of the iconic Saravana Bhavan in India. It's strictly for those who miss good south Indian food and haven't been to Chennai/India in a long time - Beggars can't be Choosers!! For those traveling and can't do without vegetarian food, it's a good choice and you won't be disappointed. Until now the only good south Indian food option I have found in Malaysia is at "HOME" :-)
Definitely great experience eating here. Brand has a premium, so not the cheapest place around.. If you want quality, eat here

A tantalizing treat guaranteed to make any food lover drool. Made moments before serving, at least that's what it seemed. Got a pretty good portion size for a relatively reasonable price. Would definitely recommend stopping by at least once.
The food is always good, the place is clean and the staff are helpful
Not bad - dosas aren’t great but most everything else is. Chilli Govi is recommended if you like spicy.

Whole Foods always has good customer service the employees are always willing to answer any questions you have. Yesterday I was at the one at Carlisle I could actually make a day of it. They have so much to choose from and their deli are definitely to die for. The only one thing is I wish the prices were a little lower. The bakery is also very good. 👍👍👍🤔and the thought full sign is hoping they will drop their prices a bit.

Stopped here while traveling to visit family. Bought from the salad bar and the best organic cherry tomatoes for my son. Very nice store and was busy. Surprised by the mention of Amazon prime memberships at the register when paying them

The quality of food here is plummeting. I have found dirt in my ground beef twice now: two weeks in a row. Recently we found plastic in the clam chowder. Its not really what I would expect from Whole foods. I would like to continue shopping here but I am a little worried.

I only come here for the unhealthy food or when I really want some good meat or cheese. I don't give a hoot about the healthy organic all natural buzzword food. Personally, it's overrated, overpriced, and not worth it. But that bakery? I will eat all 1000 calories of that tiny little cake. No regrets. 
Good selection of cheese, great place for fresh meat and local coffee. 

Also, there seems to be bar soap everywhere. Really.. it seemed every 2-3 aisles there was a display for some sort of soap. So much so that I'm beginning to think that this Whole Foods location is trying to tell us we smell bad. Well jokes on you Whole Foods! I showered at least twice since I last visited 3 months ago! 

Generally very friendly staff though! Even if they think we smell bad..
Can I get a smile from anyone in this place? Healthy living what about been good to one another.  $ changes people.  #compassion #bekind #smile

I went for my birthday and had an excellent meal - just can’t believe I had to keep my jacket on. There were other members of the public who were sitting in T-shirt’s. Apart from that exceptional food. Can’t complain

After 20 year's have finally returned...and no this is not just old school French. But French food at it's best, chicken breast that melted in the mouth i had to ask how was cooked. Staff knowlegable and friendly.
Yes, this is prim and proper but go treat yourself, look at offers.
I think now for me  a regular London haunt.

Highly recommend this restaurant to vegetarians and carnivores alike. The vegetarian menu lives up to its name and is truly exceptional, and the wine pairing is just an added treat. All of the dishes were cooked and prepared to an enormously high standard where technique and presentation had been given a lot of attention without sacrificing richness in flavour. I almost lost hope in French vegetarian food after my recent visit at Restaurant Gordon Ramsay, but Le Gavroche restored my faith in vegetarian-friendly French fine-dining. Will happily return very soon.

Absolutely delightful! Flawless service, flawless food. Service was perfectly balanced between formal and informal. Made to feel very welcome. Lovely relaxed ambiance. I can't think of even one area on which they can improve! Very good service also by the lady opening the door to the restaurant (you need to ring the bell on arrival) and welcomed us, hung up our coats, and bade us farewell on leaving.
My wife and I had the fixed price lunch and it was amazing. Such great food, drinks and staff. The ambience in the reataurant was also good.
